<br>
In another thread it was said that your skill in a particular spell line (like divination) has nothing to do with the duration of the spell.  Ok then, what does?<br>
Please explain for me why the Sup Camo duration varies so greatly from cast to cast.<br>
Is it simply because it's random?  Are all divination spells of random duration or just Sup Camo?<br>
<br>
What about DOTs? I'm thinking they are of fixed duration with damage dependent on the caster's level and what the mob is doing, ie rooted vs. chasing you (kiting) vs. engaging a PC.  Correct?<br>
<br>
What about buffs?  I'm thinking it's simply the level of the caster.  The higher the caster the longer the buff lasts.  Not including other variables like focus items or AA points and whatnot...<br>
<br>
The only thing that your skill in a particular spell line affects is the fizzle rate, right?  Specialization gives a chance to cast at a reduced mana cost and that's it.  No other benefits for either of those two.<br>
<br>
Tell me, do I have a firm grasp of this spell casting stuff or am I just whistling &quot;Dixie&quot;?<br>
<br>
Dig.<br>
Bibbe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utatankawd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tatankawd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/25/02 1:15:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27705.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sup Camo and other spell duration</span><hr size=1> Buffs have a fixed duration regardless of caster's level (though AA abilities and focus items CAN increase their duration).<br>
<br>
The lone exception to this rule is invis/camo/ITU.  Though the &quot;Superior&quot; versions are fixed length, and self only.  The duration of the standard forms is totally random.<br>
<br>
DoTs are fixed duration (focus not withstanding), and fixed damage.  Well, Druid DoTs, at least.<br>
<br>
Debuffs are fixed length, with the exception of roots, charms, and maybe fears (not sure about fear).  Though debuffing MR helps them to last longer.  And they all have a max duration.<br>
<br>
Specialization DOES help reduce fizzle rates, though this will really only be noticable with spells near your level, and those with &quot;broken&quot; fizzle rates (Breath of Ro, for one).<br>
<br>
Tat <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=238695">Tatanka</a> WolfDancer, 60th Druid<BR>
Snookims Whinzlow, 50th Enchanter<BR>
Silvara Drakonsbane, 48th Druid<BR>
Bigith Dwigus, 48th Warrior<BR>
Logic of War, 7th Hammer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufwinpeaks.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fwin Peaks</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/25/02 1:30:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27705.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sup Camo and other spell duration</span><hr size=1> Clarification - the 'Improved Superior' is fixed length.  The level 19 druid one is still random.  The only diff is that it is indoor-usable. <p>Fwin Peaks <BR>
55 <BR>
Hairy Front and <BR> Leatherfoot Breeder <BR>
Druzzil Ro <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/25/02 2:41:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27705.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Dixie</span><hr size=1> Heh...you're not just whistling Dixie, you have a brass band accompanying you.<br>
<br>
Tat covered most of it, I believe.  Here are some clarifications:<br>
<br>
<b>In another thread it was said that your skill in a particular spell line (like divination) has nothing to do with the duration of the spell. Ok then, what does? Please explain for me why the Sup Camo duration varies so greatly from cast to cast.  Is it simply because it's random? </b><br>
<br>
It's random.<br>
<br>
<br>
<b>What about DOTs? I'm thinking they are of fixed duration with damage dependent on the caster's level and what the mob is doing, ie rooted vs. chasing you (kiting) vs. engaging a PC. Correct?</b><br>
<br>
Base damage is fixed and does not vary with caster level.  It does get adjusted based on the status of the mob at the end of the tick when damage is applied.  It will be reduced by 33% if the mob is in chase mode, or will be increased by about 12% if rooted, engaged, or fleeing.<br>
<br>
<b>What about buffs? I'm thinking it's simply the level of the caster. The higher the caster the longer the buff lasts. Not including other variables like focus items or AA points and whatnot...</b><br>
<br>
As noted above, buffs are basically constant duration, and independent of caster level.<br>
<br>
<br>
<b>The only thing that your skill in a particular spell line affects is the fizzle rate, right? Specialization gives a chance to cast at a reduced mana cost and that's it. No other benefits for either of those two.</b><br>
<br>
Specialization does affect your fizzle rate AND mana expenditure.  Fizzle rate is covered above.  The mana reduction from spec is constant, there is no specialization check or chance to cast at a reduced coast.  The amount of the reduction increases with spec level.<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A> at: 6/25/02 2:50:26 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utatankawd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tatankawd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/25/02 4:24:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27705.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dixie</span><hr size=1> Thanks, Fwin, I meant &quot;Improved&quot; versions, not &quot;Superior&quot;.<br>
