Logic of War, 7th Hammer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubibbe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bibbe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/26/02 6:36:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27705.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Dixie</span><hr size=1> &quot;As noted above, buffs are basically constant duration, and independent of caster level.&quot;<br>
<br>
Then why can't I &quot;refresh&quot; someone's sow all the time?<br>
<br>
What I mean is, every now and again I get that message &quot;your spell did not take hold&quot; or whatever it says exactly...  I figured it meant that someone already had sow (or something even faster/better, like soe or something) on them, cast by a higher level toon.  If sow (for example, other buffs too though, skin like X and whatnot) has the same duration when it's cast by a level 12 druid vs. a level 60 then I should be able to overwrite any caster's sow every time.  Right?<br>
<br>
and Thanks for all the details...  I LOVE this board.<br>
