Bibbe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/26/02 7:16:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27705.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dixie</span><hr size=1> <b>...has the same duration when it's cast by a level 12 druid vs. a level 60 then I should be able to overwrite any caster's sow every time. Right?</b><br>
<br>
Incorrect.  SoW, in fact, is one of those spells that increases in speed based on level for several levels before capping.  A higher level character casting SoW is not refreshing an existing SoW cast by a lower level player, it's replacing it.<br>
<br>
And whether one spell overwrites another has nothing to do with duration.  It's usually (usually, mind you) based on the type of spell effects and relative levels of the caster.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utatankawd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tatankawd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/26/02 12:26:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27705.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dixie</span><hr size=1> Correct, the DURATION of buffs does not increase with casters level, but often the DEGREE of benefit does increase.<br>
<br>
SoW was mentioned.  Clarity is another good example.  When Chanters get it at 29, it's 4 mana/tick, increasing at 32, 40, and finally at 48 when it's 7/tick.  If a level 47 chanter tries to give me clarity, it will &quot;not take hold&quot; if I have clarity from a 48 chanter.  But a clarity from a 29 chanter and a 48 chanter both last 27 minutes.<br>
<br>
